values: Okay yeah...it is really sad, but I don't even know what teams are playing in the Superbowl. I have been a little bit out of the loop. I however, will be at work through the entirity of the game. It's all good though! I love my job. My guess is that we won't be all that busy, but perhaps we may. Who knows. It's soooo hard to guestimate a Sunday. Things are going well here though. Jeremy and I are doing pretty well. School is going well. And TIP is going pretty well. I haven't gone on call yet, but that will change on WED. I picked up two more days to be on call soooo...yeah. I am a little nervous about going on my first call. I will definitly have to read up on some of my EFA's. And just some of the other reading material. Other than that, I feel pretty organized. I have my portfolio together and I think that I will be fine. I hope. Aghh....just a little nervous and ambivalent. Well I have to run due to the fact that I have to finish homework, start studying for my final and then head off to work. Ahhh....yes. Anways, Ciao for now!!

So I am sitting here at the computer and I only just got home from an 11 hour shift, and I am still amazed as to how time has flown. School just ended for me on wed. and in 15 days it'll be Christmas, and in 16 days I will be moving to Pensacola, FL. Again. I am really excited to go back. Things are going a lot better for me here and I am just thankful for each day. I've been given a new lease on life. Hahah...but seriously. Things didn't quite pan out in Portland like I wanted. Well...I got accepted to Portland State University but am unable to attend to do the high cost of out of state tuition and the fact that I am not quite eligible for a loan. Plus the confusion of transferring credits to their scale is just...interesting. But other than that things are going pretty well. I still can't believe that it is December already. Where did the time go? Well anyways.... I am off to go and read a book and then to bed it is for me. Soo..ciao for now.

Love Alway,

Chrissy

I was at my friends apartment until like 1:30 am and I was like...well so much for that sleep. I was up at 6:45 am and then I was at school until almost 4:00 pm. All's I know is that I already have quite a few assignments that I have to jump on! I have a quiz already on wed. in Human Biology and then I have an essay and a current event response paper due in Intro to Sociology. In Math I have two assignments. So tomorrow...on top of job hunting I have a lot of work to do! Well I am going to go and get some coffee so that I can stay up and begin my work! Okay well ciao for now!

I am just homesick and sad from not seeing everyone everyday! I just got accustomed to being around some of the same people everyday 24/7 for 7 1/2 weeks! So it is definitly a weird transition! I just can't wait to go to back to school on Monday! Once I get started I know it will be great! Yeah well I just need to stay positive!!! I am sooooo bored!! I feel like I have nothing to do! I mean I have plenty but nothing exciting! I really need to unpack and do my laundry and all of that fun jazz but I just don't feel like it today! I am still adjusting to the time change. After spending my entire summer in Pacific time I am now back in Eastern time. Gross! Anyways yeah thats all I really have to say for now!!! I am bored, bored, bored, bored!!!!!!

Okay well....I am back at home. I am not sure whether or not I should be happy or sad. I really miss everyone. It is sooo weird right now not seeing everyone that I have lived with for 7 1/2 weeks. I am excited to back at home in one sense and not so much in another. The silence is a little strange to. I mean hearing the T.V instead of music and girls and guys alike singing is weird. Also, I have my own room right now. Crazy. Also I have clean feet and my own bathroom. Ahhhh....soooo nice. No more unclogging toilets, well....I didn't do it half as much as liane. No certainly not even close. School starts for me in a week and I am looking forward to that. Tomorrow I have to go job hunting and I have to start unpacking. I am definitly not looking forward to that. I also have to start applying to colleges out west. I really want to move to Portland/Vancouver area by January. That is my goal!!! Yay!!! Okay well...I am going to head out for now! I am sooo tired and I promised one of my friends that I would go and pick her up so we can hang out! Soooo nice to have my own car again! Ahhh....the freedom! Okay well peace and love to you all!


Love Always,
Chris
